{
  "texts": [
    "Erroneous assumptions regarding causality can result in flawed assessments of fairness.",
    "Decision trees and rule-based systems, owing to their interpretability, facilitate the understanding of algorithmic decisions.",
    "However, their simplicity may be a limitation as they may not adequately address the complexities inherent in various data sets.",
    "To mitigate some of the discussed shortcomings, supervised ranking, unsupervised regression, and reinforcement in fairness evaluation can be approached through pairwise evaluation [50].",
    "This technique involves assessing an AI model's performance by comparing its outputs against a preselected set of input data pairs."
  ]
}